Conſiſtory (ſays one) is the Counſel-Houſe of Eccleſiaſtical Perſons; and it is a word borrowed of the Italians;


                              〈…〉
                           . f. 338. or rather, the Lombards: and ſignifies as much as Tribunal. It is Vocabulum utriuſque Juris; and is uſed for the place of Juſtice, in the Courts Chriſtian, or Spiritual.

This Excommunication thus defined by the Canoniſt, is twofold;

                           Co. Lit. 133 b.
                         it is either Leſſer, or Greater.
